# BudgetTrackerApp

A simple Java-based budget tracker to manage your incomes and expenses. The application supports adding expenses and incomes, tracking budgets, and displaying reports.

## 🚀 Features

- Add and edit expenses
- Add and edit incomes
- View expense reports
- Budget tracking
- Simple GUI built with Swing

## 📂 Project Structure

- `AddExpenseWindow.java` - handles the Add Expense dialog
- `AddIncomeWindow.java` - handles the Add Income dialog
- `BudgetManager.java` - core business logic
- `BudgetMenu.java` - menu bar GUI logic
- `BudgetTrackerApp.java` - main application entry point
- `Expense.java` - expense data model
- `Income.java` - income data model

## ⚙️ Requirements

- Java 17 or later
- Eclipse IDE (optional, but recommended)
- Git (to contribute)

## 🛠️ Setup Instructions

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/yourusername/BudgetTrackerApp.git
Open the project in Eclipse:

File → Import → Existing Maven or Java Project → select the folder

Build the project and run BudgetTrackerApp.java as a Java Application.

💻 Usage
From the main window, click on Add Expense to record an expense.

Click Add Income to record an income.

View your budget summary on the main screen.

